<font color="#FF0000">MY THOUGHTS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Oct 22 13:50:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
There is nothing more damaging to a society than the wailing, whining, and public exhortations of those who have built their platform from the bodies of my fallen brothers.  Let them know that the place where they stand is secure only because of the sacrifice and commitment of those men.  No nation has ever endured with a pacifist mentality.  It would be foolish for us to think we can police the world and suicidal to imagine we do not have to defend our freedom and ideologies.  Who then are the chosen few who must risk their life for the country and most important who has the right to choose.  Not the pacifist who feels he needs his freedom at the expense of another.
